<article>
<blockquote class="messageText SelectQuoteContainer ugc baseHtml">
I took the liberty of looking for some good spells we could potentially cast, once casting spells is a thing. I know that&#039;s a ways out right now, but we&#039;re going to do it eventually, so it&#039;s worth thinking about.<br/>
<br/>
<ul>
<li>Selesnya Charm: Can get rid of any one thing big enough to actually threaten Regina, or save a sliver, Regina, or Gil from combat/make them win combat, or summon a 2/2 creature. All of those modes seem good, and at only 2 mana and with such versatility, it seems like a steal.</li>
<li>Evolution Charm: I&#039;m thinking of this as a recon tool for replacing mana bonds after a shift. The searching for a basic land mode could be interpreted as telling us what the changed land has become and the flight mode can get Regina there and back quickly so she can mana bond efficiently, even if we haven&#039;t spawned a Winged Sliver yet. The raise dead effect can bring back any specials we might lose, as well.</li>
<li>Hearth Charm: Great against mechanical races, or gives attacking sliver armies a decent boost, or makes one small sliver into an unstoppable assassin for a turn (possibly in combination with the deathtouch granting sliver). Needs red mana, but we know where some mountains are.</li>
<li>Atarka&#039;s Command: I don&#039;t know what face damage does in this, but preventing lifegain, pumping our army, and putting a land into play (can we interpret this as making a mana bond as a free action at the risk of destabilizing two of our other mana bonds?) all seem like good things to be doing.</li>
<li>Dromoka&#039;s Command: Blocks some types of magic, makes a sliver a bit bigger permanently, dispels persistent magics, and lets us pick off specific enemies at the cost of damage to Regina or some other big sliver. </li>
<li>Rampant Growth/Explosive Vegetation/Cultivate, etc.: Mo&#039; mana!</li>
<li>Plague Wind: Obviously expensive, but boy is it effective.</li>
</ul>
<div class="messageTextEndMarker">&nbsp;</div>
</blockquote>
</article>
