<div class="messageInfo primaryContent">
<div class="messageContent">
<article>
<blockquote class="messageText SelectQuoteContainer ugc baseHtml">
[X] Doubling down<br/>
<br/>
We have 16 actions from the eight 1/1 slivers &amp; 3 queen actions<br/>
<br/>
<br/>
Survey: 4 sliver actions<br/>
Build: Add to our hives defences, Gill&#039;s weapons will be rapidly depleted of ammo if that&#039;s all we have as a defence. 7 sliver actions<br/>
Hunt: we need 11 food this turn. Use 1 action from queen (2d6) + 2 from the slivers (2d1) (cap 15)<br/>
Research: Learn fire from Gil. We need this to permanently deal with the Ork spores, and it helps towards food preservation later. 1 sliver action<br/>
Patrol: just around our base, and staying clear of the Elves. 1 sliver action<br/>
Learn Language: English to 2/3 (Queen)<br/>
Social: Try and convince the Elves we&#039;re friendly, and want to cooperate with them against the Orks. If we can make an Elven friend this turn, put learning English on hold next turn to learn Elvish. 1 sliver action<br/>
Mana Bond: This part of the forest is quite dense with optimal locations;<br/>
IF: Social is successful, bond the closest point to the hive that is inside their territory.<br/>
ELSE: bond the closest point that isn&#039;t inside Elvish territory.<br/>
<br/>
<a href="https://forums.sufficientvelocity.com/members/10324/" class="username" data-user="10324, @eaglejarl">@eaglejarl</a> Does Gil have any actions, can we assign him any tasks?
