Now that we have a crapton of generics, Queen Only Actions are at a serious premium. We should not be using her for anything that doesn&#039;t get an advantage or is unique.<br/>
<br/>
I think we should do Hunt/Learn English/Mana Bond with the queen right now. And Hunt only because we should get what we can out of the +2 while we have it.<br/>
<br/>
Fire Research could be started by a generic&#039;s action which will at least give us the amount needed to complete it. I actually think we should be doing Magic research first, on <a href="http://gatherer.wizards.com/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=giant+growth" target="_blank" class="externalLink" rel="nofollow">Giant Growth</a>.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="http://gatherer.wizards.com/Handlers/Image.ashx?multiverseid=393898&amp;type=card" class="bbCodeImage LbImage" alt="[&#x200B;IMG]" data-url="http://gatherer.wizards.com/Handlers/Image.ashx?multiverseid=393898&amp;type=card"/><br/>
<br/>
It is the most basic and iconic Green spell (the mana we have best access to), and it both can help up with the food situation, and help us in combat by making ourselves huge. It should be the start of the Green mana tech tree, most of which is buff and growth based spells - the thing we need the most right now with a small number of units versus an enormous army of mooks.<br/>
<br/>
We should learn Giant Growth, and then send out Growth&#039;d raiders at the Ork camp to capture Squigs.<br/>
<br/>
From there, we should look at Untamed Wilds<br/>
<br/>
<img src="http://gatherer.wizards.com/Handlers/Image.ashx?multiverseid=11549&amp;type=card" class="bbCodeImage LbImage" alt="[&#x200B;IMG]" data-url="http://gatherer.wizards.com/Handlers/Image.ashx?multiverseid=11549&amp;type=card"/><br/>
<br/>
Which should massively increase our mana gain rate.
