<div class="bbCodeBlock bbCodeQuote" data-author="Pahan">
<aside>
<div class="attribution type">Pahan said:
<a href="goto/post?id=5531414#post-5531414" class="AttributionLink">&uarr;</a>
</div>
<blockquote class="quoteContainer"><div class="quote">If we aren&#039;t spawning next turn, I don&#039;t think we need to mana-bond this turn. Do you think we will? My sense is that the carrying capacity of the area might not allow it. If we hunt this turn, we can free up two (I think) generics for scouting and patrol.</div><div class="quoteExpand">Click to expand...</div></blockquote>
</aside>
</div>Remember that bonds also prevent chaos shifts from messing up the local landscape. The more forest we claim the less likely it is for us to suddenly be stuck in some arctic tundra or worse with no places to get enough food. And since we both need mana in the long run and that action can only be done by Regina herself keeping up a decent amount of bonding is smart IMO.
<div class="messageTextEndMarker">&nbsp;</div>
</blockquote>
</article>
