<div class="messageInfo primaryContent">
<div class="messageContent">
<article>
<blockquote class="messageText SelectQuoteContainer ugc baseHtml">
<div class="bbCodeBlock bbCodeQuote" data-author="Pahan">
<aside>
<div class="attribution type">Pahan said:
<a href="goto/post?id=5531513#post-5531513" class="AttributionLink">&uarr;</a>
</div>
<blockquote class="quoteContainer"><div class="quote">It depends on how big an area we&#039;ve bonded already, I guess, but also the fact that there is a lot of contiguous forest here suggests that we are extremely unlikely to lose it all at once.</div><div class="quoteExpand">Click to expand...</div></blockquote>
</aside>
</div>That depends, we haven&#039;t gotten the mechanics of chaos shifts yet. They might simply change everything around all at once sometimes. All we know is that claiming the forest means we get to keep it if we don&#039;t use it. And forest is bound to be some of the best terrain for food production. And as our numbers increase we&#039;ll need a lot of food producing terrain. Might as well claim as much as we can now. Our queen actions are probably only going to get more valuable as time goes on.
<div class="messageTextEndMarker">&nbsp;</div>
</blockquote>
</article>
